02:32

GreyDuckNebula 26-Oct-22 03:34 AM
Also, I know you work a lot with a producer, but do have tips on how to get a song to have a more full and professional sound
TheDecemberAir 26-Oct-22 03:34 AM
EQ is big.
03:35
Knowing when and where to cut and roll different frequencies so they fit better together so the whole song doesn‚Äôt sound like a muddy mess is important cus that‚Äôs your base
03:36
I do some of it to an extent but it gets really complicated for like top of the line stuff
03:38
Also layering. Layer your synths, pianos, strings, etc. Find sounds that fit well together and have them play the same notes, but an octave higher or lower. Or some variation of that.
03:38
I‚Äôd also say make sure you have one stand out layer and the rest be more complimentary
03:38
So don‚Äôt have them all at the same volume
03:40
Panning sounds are big too. Make your mixes sound wider. If everything is coming from the same spot, and you don‚Äôt pan certain instruments left or right at all, it can muddy everything and sound one dimensional
